// Material: Character Skin Variation Master Material
// This represents the master material for character skin variations

/*
Material Configuration:
- Shading Model: Default Lit
- Blend Mode: Opaque
- Material Domain: Surface

Parameters:
- SkinTone (Scalar): Controls skin color from light to dark
- DirtLevel (Scalar): Controls dirt/grime overlay intensity
- ScarLevel (Scalar): Controls scar visibility and intensity
- WearLevel (Scalar): Controls clothing wear and tear
- SubsurfaceScattering (Vector3): Skin SSS color
- Roughness (Scalar): Skin surface roughness
- Normal Intensity (Scalar): Normal map strength

Texture Inputs:
- BaseColor_Texture (Texture2D): Base skin color map
- Normal_Texture (Texture2D): Skin normal map
- Roughness_Texture (Texture2D): Skin roughness map
- Dirt_Overlay_Texture (Texture2D): Dirt and grime overlay
- Scar_Mask_Texture (Texture2D): Scar placement mask
- Subsurface_Texture (Texture2D): Subsurface scattering map

Material Graph:
1. Base skin color modified by SkinTone parameter
2. Dirt overlay blended based on DirtLevel
3. Scar details added based on ScarLevel
4. Normal maps combined for skin detail
5. Roughness adjusted for realistic skin properties
6. Subsurface scattering for realistic skin translucency

This material works with MetaHuman meshes to create diverse, realistic character appearances
that reflect the harsh survival conditions of the prehistoric world.
*/

// This file represents the material structure that would be created in UE5 Material Editor
// The actual material would be built using the node-based material editor